{{Infobox cycling race report | name = Women's omnium | image = UEC Champion Jersey.svg | image_caption = [[UEC European Champion jersey]] | image_size = 150px | series = [[2008 European Track Championships]] | race_no = | series_no = | date = 3 September 2008 | stages = 1 | type = medals | first = [[Elena Tchalykh]] | first_nat = Russia | first_natvar = | first_team = | second = [[Ellen van Dijk]] | second_nat = the Netherlands | second_natvar = | second_team = | third = [[Anastasia Tchulkova]] | third_nat = Russia | third_natvar = | third_team = | previous = [[2007 European Track Championships – Women's omnium|2007]] | next = [[2009 European Track Championships – Women's omnium|2009]] }} {{main|2008 European Track Championships}}
The '''Women's Omnium''' was the only elite women's events at the [[2008 European Track Championships]] held in [[Pruszków]], Poland and took place at 3 September. The omnium consisted of four events: [[Elimination races|elimination race]], [[scratch race]], 3000m [[individual pursuit]] and a [[points race]]. Seventeen cyclists participated in the women's omnium.<ref>{{cite web|title=European Championship, Track, Omnium, Elite (F) 2008|url=http://www.cyclingarchives.com/ritfiche.php?ritid=124194#first|publisher=www.cyclingarchives.com|date=3 September 2008}}</ref><ref name=UCI /><ref name=tissot />
