'''Darrell Bailey''' (born {{birth based on age as of date |50|2018|July|20|noage=1}}),<ref name=streeter_06202018>{{cite news|last=Streeter|first=Kurt|title=Clipper Darrell Won’t Bow to King James. But He Wants To.|date=July 20, 2018|newspaper=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/07/20/sports/basketball/clipper-darrell-lakers.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180721112706/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/07/20/sports/basketball/clipper-darrell-lakers.html|archivedate=July 21, 2017|deadurl=no}}</ref> better known as '''Clipper Darrell''', is a [[wikt:superfan|superfan]] of the [[Los Angeles Clippers]] of the [[National Basketball Association]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Beck |first=Howard |title=NBA: Clipper fans savor moment of glory |date=May 12, 2006 |newspaper=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/05/12/sports/12iht-CLIPPERS.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/65qIy6YzM?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2006/05/12/sports/12iht-CLIPPERS.html |archivedate=March 1, 2012 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> A [[season ticket]] holder since the [[2000–01 Los Angeles Clippers season|2000–01 season]], he dances, leads cheers, and taunts the opposing team at [[home game]]s in a half red, half blue suit—the Clippers' team colors.<ref name=markazi_05112009>{{cite news|last=Markazi |first=Arash |title=A Clippers fan 'til the end -- almost |date=May 11, 2009 |work=SI.com |url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/2009/writers/arash_markazi/04/28/clipper-darrell/?eref=T1 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100105010536/http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/2009/writers/arash_markazi/04/28/clipper-darrell/?eref=T1 |archivedate=January 5, 2010 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Come to L.A., LeBron: Clippers fans hold parade in James' honor |date=May 28, 2010 |agency=Associated Press |work=Cleaveland.com |url=http://www.cleveland.com/cavs/index.ssf/2010/05/come_to_la_lebron_clippers_fan.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/65qLxnVqb?url=http://www.cleveland.com/cavs/index.ssf/2010/05/come_to_la_lebron_clippers_fan.html |archivedate=March 1, 2012 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> One of his usual chants is "Let's go Clippers!". A personal favorite of his is "U-G-L-Y, you ain’t got no alibi, you ugly!", which he directs at opposing players when they shoot [[free throw]]s.<ref name=markazi_05112009/><ref name=coro>{{cite news |last=Coro |first=Paul |title=Fight breaks out in 4th quarter of Phoenix Suns vs. Los Angeles Clippers game |date=April 4, 2013 |work=azcentral.com |url=http://www.azcentral.com/sports/suns/articles/20130403phoenix-suns-skid-reaches-games-with-loss-at-los-angeles-clippers.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6FpTnLZcZ?url=http://www.azcentral.com/sports/suns/articles/20130403phoenix-suns-skid-reaches-games-with-loss-at-los-angeles-clippers.html?nclick_check=1 |archivedate=April 12, 2013 |deadurl=no |df= }}</ref> He is one of the few remaining clean [[heckler]]s in the NBA.<ref name=streeter_06202018/><ref name=coro/>
Bailey drives a customized 1995 [[BMW 7 Series|BMW 740i]], whose exterior and interior are each red, white, and blue. The hood features a Clippers logo and autographs, and the license plates are customized with ''CLIPERD''.<ref name=markazi_05112009/> His home in [[Los Angeles]] is painted in the team's colors with a red, white and blue [[basketball court]] in the driveway and a Clippers logo on the pavement. The front door is red, and the living room is white and blue with Clippers logos prominent from the walls to the floor tiles.<ref name=markazi_05112009/><ref name=markazi_02292012>{{cite news|last=Markazi |first=Arash |title='Clipper Darrell,' Clippers butt heads |date=February 29, 2012 |work=ESPNLosAngeles.com |url=http://espn.go.com/los-angeles/nba/story/_/id/7631532/darrell-bailey-says-los-angeles-clippers-asked-refrain-using-clipper-darrell-name |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/65qKkDgWj?url=http://espn.go.com/los-angeles/nba/story/_/id/7631532/darrell-bailey-says-los-angeles-clippers-asked-refrain-using-clipper-darrell-name |archivedate=March 1, 2012 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>
As a student growing up in [[South Los Angeles]], Bailey was known as a jokester. He held various jobs after dropping out of [[community college]].<ref name=streeter_06202018/> In 1984, he was fired from his job and told by his boss that he would "never amount to anything". After hearing an announcer say the same about the Clippers, he decided to support the team. He was originally known as '''Dancing Man''' before changing to Clipper Darrell after a few radio appearances.<ref name=markazi_05112009/> He attended 386&nbsp;consecutive games until the streak was broken by a trip to the hospital for high blood pressure.<ref>{{cite news |last=Lin |first=Dennis |title=Not Your Typical Fan |date=October 26, 2010 |work=NBA.com |url=http://www.nba.com/clippers/features/lin_101026.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101101194422/http://www.nba.com/clippers/features/lin_101026.html |archivedate=November 1, 2010 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> ''[[The New York Times]]'' called him "the team’s unofficial biggest fan".<ref>{{cite news |last=Gold |first=Jon |title=Remaking a B-Movie in Los Angeles |newspaper=The New York Times |page=SP7 |date=January 30, 2011 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/01/30/sports/basketball/30clippers.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/65qMQiRZY?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2011/01/30/sports/basketball/30clippers.html?_r%3D1 |archivedate=March 1, 2012 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> The ''[[Wall Street Journal]]'' wrote, "He’s perhaps the only superfan in the history of the Los Angeles Clippers."<ref>{{cite news|last=Gordon |first=Jeremy |title=The Ballad of Clipper Darrell |date=March 1, 2012 |newspaper=The Wall Street Journal |url=https://blogs.wsj.com/dailyfix/2012/03/01/nba-los-angeles-clippers-the-ballad-of-clipper-darrell/ |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/65qNW49yh?url=http://blogs.wsj.com/dailyfix/2012/03/01/nba-los-angeles-clippers-the-ballad-of-clipper-darrell/ |archivedate=March 1, 2012 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> He is not an employee of the Clippers organization. In February 2012, there was a dispute with the team over the use of ''Clipper'' in his name.<ref name=markazi_02292012/> The Clippers accused him of capitalizing on the ''Clipper'' name, but later reached a mutual agreement that Bailey would notify the Clippers when appearing publicly as ''Clipper Darrell''.<ref>{{cite news|last=Gleeson |first=Scott |title=Longtime fan Clipper Darrell is back |date=March 19, 2012 |newspaper=USA Today |url=http://content.usatoday.com/communities/gameon/post/2012/03/longtime-fan-clipper-darrell-is-back/1#.T30fFtmXx8E |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/66gmaognv?url=http://content.usatoday.com/communities/gameon/post/2012/03/longtime-fan-clipper-darrell-is-back/1 |archivedate=April 5, 2012 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>
In 2014, former Clippers co-owner [[Shelly Sterling]] received the title of "Clippers Number One Fan” as part of the sales agreement with incoming owner [[Steve Ballmer]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Bolch |first1=Ben |last2=Fenno |first2=Nathan |last3=Rohlin |first3=Melissa |title=Steve Ballmer is officially new owner of Clippers, NBA says |date=August 12, 2014 |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |url=http://www.latimes.com/sports/sportsnow/la-sp-sn-nba-steve-ballmer-owner-clippers-20140812-story.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6SGz0CIG3?url=http://www.latimes.com/sports/sportsnow/la-sp-sn-nba-steve-ballmer-owner-clippers-20140812-story.html |archivedate=September 1, 2014 |deadurl=no |df= }}</ref> [[Yahoo! Sports]], however, opined that Clipper Darrell was "the Clippers No. 1 fan, no matter what official documents say."<ref>{{cite news|last=Freeman |first=Eric |title=Clipper Darrell is willing to let Shelly Sterling share the title of 'Clippers No. 1 Fan' |date=August 19, 2014 |work=yahoo.com |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/blogs/nba-ball-dont-lie/clipper-darrell-is-willing-to-let-shelly-sterling-share-the-title-of--clippers-no--1-fan-002241974.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6SGzKf30r?url=http://sports.yahoo.com/blogs/nba-ball-dont-lie/clipper-darrell-is-willing-to-let-shelly-sterling-share-the-title-of--clippers-no--1-fan-002241974.html |archivedate=September 1, 2014 |deadurl=no |df= }}</ref>
Bailey has a wife and four children.<ref name=markazi_02292012/>
