{{Infobox Stadium | stadium_name = Estadio Cibao FC | logo_image = | image =https://goo.gl/images/1Q9d9L | caption = | location = [[Santiago de los Caballeros]], Santiago, Dominican Republic | coordinates = {{coords|19|26|43|N|70|47|47|W|display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = 2015 | opened = March 8, 2015 (stadium) | owner = Cibao FC | operator = | surface = [[FieldTurf]] | tenants = [[Cibao FC]] }} '''Stadium Cibao FC''' is a football [[stadium]] in [[Santiago de los Caballeros]], [[Dominican Republic]]. It is currently used for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and hosts the home games of [[Cibao FC]] of the [[Liga Dominicana de Fútbol]]. The stadium holds 10,000 spectators.
The stadium opened on March 8, 2015, hosting the sold-out inaugural match of the [[Liga Dominicana de Fútbol]] between Cibao and [[Atlético Vega Real]].<ref>{{cite news |date=March 10, 2015 |title=Dominican Republic launches professional league |url=http://www.concacaf.com/article/dominican-republic-launches-professional-league-3 |publisher=[[CONCACAF]] |accessdate=December 6, 2017}}</ref> Later that month, the [[Dominican Republic national football team]] hosted a friendly against [[Cuba national football team|Cuba]] at the stadium, lost 3–0.<ref>{{cite news |date=March 27, 2015 |title=Early goals point Cuba past the Dominican Republic |url=http://www.concacaf.com/article/early-goals-point-cuba-past-the-dominican-republic |publisher=CONCACAF |accessdate=December 6, 2017}}</ref>
==References== {{reflist|30em}}
==External links== *{{official website|http://www.cibaofc.com/}}
[[Category:Football venues in the Dominican Republic]] [[Category:Santiago de los Caballeros]] [[Category:2015 establishments in the Dominican Republic]] [[Category:Sports venues completed in 2015]]

The practice of '''[[futsal]]''' in Paraguay is very popular and is one of the most practiced sports in the country. The governing body for futsal in Paraguay is the [[Asociación Paraguaya de Fútbol]] (Paraguayan football association), which controls the [[Paraguay national futsal team]] and is in charge of the organization of the [[Campeonato de Futsal de Paraguay]] (Paraguayan futsal tournament).

The Paraguayan futsal tournament is being held since 1987, declaring a champion every year. Since 1995  a new system consisting of two tournaments ([[Apertura]] and [[Clausura]]) was created, in which the national champion is declared by facing the winners of the Apertura and Clausura. Another tournament called "De Campeones" was also introduced. In 2004, a second division tournament was created to allow for more teams to compete.

At the national team level, Paraguay has won three [[FIFUSA/AMF Futsal World Cup|AMF Futsal World Cups]], a bronze medal at the [[Pan American Games]] and one [[South American Futsal Championship]].

